================================================================================
SolarFlare fork (https://github.com/vindeckyy/Solar-Flare)
================================================================================

The SolarFlare fork is a derivative of upstream LizardByte/Sunshine
(https://github.com/LizardByte/Sunshine), copyright the LizardByte
maintainers and contributors, distributed under the GPL-3.0-only
license. The fork's own contributions are documented in
docs/CHANGELOG-SolarFlare.md and consist primarily of:

* 5 Linux-only configuration keys (`busy_poll_us`, `rate_cap_pct`,
  `enet_4mib_buffer`, `pipewire_latency_ms`, `cpu_pinning`) wired
  through the standard Sunshine config plumbing.
* CachyOS-native build flags (Zen 1/2/3/4 microarchitecture
  auto-detection, -march / -mtune / -O3 / -flto) in
  cmake/compile_definitions/common.cmake.
* A multi-distro build script (scripts/cachyos-build.sh) supporting
  Arch / CachyOS / Debian / Ubuntu / Fedora / Nobara / openSUSE.
* A web UI rebrand (SolarFlare logo, navbar wordmark, "SolarFlare"
  theme, fork footer pointing at vindeckyy/Solar-Flare).
* Fork-specific documentation (docs/PORTING.md,
  docs/CONFIGURATION.md, docs/CHANGELOG-SolarFlare.md,
  CONTRIBUTING.md, SECURITY.md).
* A fork-specific CI workflow (.github/workflows/ci-solarflare.yml)
  that runs scripts/cachyos-build.sh on an Arch container and
  verifies the fork banner + the 5 fork config keys + the test
  suite.
* 17 upstream-friendly overrides of the centrally-managed
  LizardByte-pinned GitHub Actions workflows, each with a one-line
  no-op explanation.
* 22 cherry-picked upstream commits (4 with manual conflict
  resolution); see docs/CHANGELOG-SolarFlare.md for the full list.
* 12 unit tests for the fork config keys in
  tests/unit/test_config_fork_keys.cpp and 5 regression tests
  for the upstream e40d355f fix(video) cherry-pick in
  tests/unit/test_thread_safe_try_pop.cpp.

All fork modifications are released under the same GPL-3.0-only
license as upstream. The fork does not claim any copyright on the
upstream Sunshine code; the upstream copyright notices and the
GPL-3.0 license text in the LICENSE file apply to the upstream
code unchanged. The fork's modifications are too small to warrant
their own copyright header; they are documented in the changelog
and git history.

For the full list of fork-specific files, see git log origin/master
--stat. For the diff between the fork and upstream, regenerate
cachyos-fastpath.patch with:

    git diff 1fce18d9..HEAD > cachyos-fastpath.patch
